          "value": "xywh=pixel:451.4907226562502,3293.1115722656255,2928.66943359375,1566.8957519531245"
        }
      },
      "@context": "http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld",
      "type": "Annotation",
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "transcribing",
          "value": "PRAISED are You, Adonai our God, Ruler of the universe,\nwho speaks the evening into being,\nskillfully opens the gates,\nthoughtfully alters the time and changes the seasons,\nand arranges the stars in their heavenly courses according to plan.\nYou are Creator of day and night,\nrolling light away from darkness and darkness from light,\ntransforming day into night and distinguishing one from the other.\nAdonai Tzvaot is Your Name.\nEver-living God, may You reign continually over us into eternity.\nPraise to You, Adonai, who brings on evening."
        }
      ],
